  "prompt": "What does \"last activity\" mean on Skype?",
  "response": "On Skype, \"last activity\" refers to the most recent time a user was active on the platform. It indicates when that user was last online or interacted with the app, which can include sending messages, making calls, or using other features. This information can be helpful for understanding when a contact was last available or may indicate their current availability status. Note that users can choose to hide their last activity status for privacy reasons, so it may not always be visible for everyone.",
